<main class="chapter-content">

<section>
    <h2>Introduction</h2>
    <p>
        Trigonometry in Paper 2 focuses on **identities, equations, double angles, and applied problems**.  
        Understanding the meaning behind ratios is key, so learners can solve problems without guessing.
    </p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Basic Trigonometric Ratios</h2>
    <p>In a right-angled triangle:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>sin θ = opposite ÷ hypotenuse</li>
        <li>cos θ = adjacent ÷ hypotenuse</li>
        <li>tan θ = opposite ÷ adjacent</li>
    </ul>
    <p>These ratios only apply in right-angled triangles.</p>

    <h3>Worked Example 1</h3>
    <p>Opposite side = 3 cm, hypotenuse = 5 cm. Find sin θ.</p>
    <ol>
        <li>Identify ratio: sin θ = opposite ÷ hypotenuse</li>
        <li>Substitute values: sin θ = 3 ÷ 5</li>
        <li>Answer: sin θ = 3/5</li>
    </ol>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>The CAST Diagram</h2>
    <p>The CAST diagram helps remember which ratios are positive in each quadrant:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>C</strong>osine – Quadrant 4</li>
        <li><strong>A</strong>ll – Quadrant 1</li>
        <li><strong>S</strong>ine – Quadrant 2</li>
        <li><strong>T</strong>angent – Quadrant 3</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Special Angles</h2>
    <p>Exact values to know: 0°, 30°, 45°, 60°, 90°</p>
    <h3>Worked Example 2</h3>
    <p>Find sin 30°</p>
    <ol>
        <li>Recall: sin 30° = 1/2</li>
        <li>Answer: 1/2</li>
    </ol>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Trigonometric Identities</h2>
    <p>Key identities:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>sin²θ + cos²θ = 1</li>
        <li>tan θ = sin θ ÷ cos θ</li>
        <li>1 + tan²θ = sec²θ</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Worked Example 3</h3>
    <p>Prove: (1 − sin²θ) / cos²θ = 1</p>
    <ol>
        <li>Start with LHS: (1 − sin²θ) / cos²θ</li>
        <li>Use identity: 1 − sin²θ = cos²θ</li>
        <li>Substitute: cos²θ / cos²θ = 1</li>
        <li>Conclusion: LHS = RHS ✔</li>
    </ol>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Solving Trigonometric Equations</h2>
    <ol>
        <li>Solve the basic equation</li>
        <li>Use CAST for additional solutions</li>
        <li>Write answers in the correct interval</li>
    </ol>

    <h3>Worked Example 4</h3>
    <p>Solve sin θ = 0.5 for 0° ≤ θ ≤ 360°</p>
    <ol>
        <li>Reference angle: θ = 30°</li>
        <li>CAST: Sine positive in Quadrants 1 & 2</li>
        <li>Solutions: θ = 30°, 150°</li>
    </ol>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Double Angle Formulae</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>sin 2θ = 2 sin θ cos θ</li>
        <li>cos 2θ = cos²θ − sin²θ</li>
        <li>tan 2θ = 2 tan θ ÷ (1 − tan²θ)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Worked Example 5</h3>
    <p>If sin θ = 1/2 and θ is acute, find sin 2θ</p>
    <ol>
        <li>cos θ = √(1 − sin²θ) = √(1 − 1/4) = √3/2</li>
        <li>sin 2θ = 2 × 1/2 × √3/2 = √3/2</li>
    </ol>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Practice Exercises</h2>
    <ol>
        <li>Find cos 60°</li>
        <li>Prove identity using sin²θ + cos²θ = 1</li>
        <li>Solve tan θ = 1 for 0° ≤ θ ≤ 360°</li>
        <li>Find sin 2θ given sin θ</li>
        <li>Sketch a sine graph and indicate amplitude and period</li>
    </ol>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Summary</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Understand ratios before formulas</li>
        <li>Use CAST for signs in all quadrants</li>
        <li>Manipulate one side only in identities</li>
        <li>Show all steps clearly</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Chapter Test</h2>
    <ol>
        <li>Prove a trigonometric identity</li>
        <li>Solve a trigonometric equation in the interval 0° ≤ θ ≤ 360°</li>
        <li>Apply double-angle formulae to find values</li>
        <li>Sketch sine and cosine graphs with transformations</li>
    </ol>
</section>

